parameters: Noble Kasaro: I'm waiting for good news.
Noble Kasaro: I can finally reach even my dreams...!
Noble Kasaro: I'll wait here for good news.

Noble Kasaro: Welcome! If there's anything I can do for you,
please let me know.

Noble Kasaro: Welcome! Please take your time and rest for a
while.
Clea: I have a reckless request to make.
Noble Kasaro: Of course, I will assist you with anything.

Noble Kasaro: The reckless request that I want you to
fulfill for me... does it involve something related to
dragons?

Clea: There is a dragon in Mount Monimos, and I would like
to request an airship to lure it out to the surface.
Clea: ...I probably won't be able to return safely.

Noble Kasaro: Of course, feel free to use that airship as
you please. It has already served its purpose in my eyes.

Noble Kasaro: If the remnants of an old man's dreams are
necessary for your future, feel free to use them as much as
you need.

Noble Kasaro: However, if I cannot provide transportation,
then the only option is to rely on the Magic Academy.

Mage Relm: I guess it would turn out like this after all...
I didn't really want to meet the Archmage if possible.

Mage Relm: I guess there's no other choice! I've also made
up my mind, let's meet the Archmage!

Noble Kasaro: I will also ask for a favor since I have
become friends with Researcher Karos-kun!
Clea: Then let's head to the Magic Academy.

Noble Kasaro: If the remnants of an old fool's dreams are
necessary for your future, feel free to use them as much as
you need.

Noble Kasaro: Oh, you've come at a good time! Did you stop
by during your adventure today?
Clea: No, I came today because I have a favor to ask.

Noble Kasaro: Hmm, I wonder if the person behind you is
involved?
Thief Nora: Um, I'll explain the details!

Noble Kasaro: I see, I see... I had heard rumors about
Campus, but I didn't expect something like this.
Thief Nora: Please! Protect the captains and everyone!

Noble Kasaro: Certainly, I want to do whatever I can to
repay the favor you've done for us.

Noble Kasaro: However, I may be an old fool who cannot
shelter a band of thieves, but I am a low-ranking noble of
the empire.
Thief Nora: Ugh, but please, I'm begging you--

Noble Kasaro: If it were a mercenary group instead of a band
of thieves, the situation would be different. This place has
become dangerous, and we need mercenaries...

Noble Kasaro: I would like to ask the leader of Ema
[Mercenary Corps] if there is a job to protect this mansion,
you see?

Captain Clevo: I am grateful for your kindness... Please
take care of my comrades...

Noble Kasaro: That's settled! Then we must also release the
[imprisoned members] unjustly.

Noble Kasaro: Now, Clevo-kun, there's no time to rest! Let's
go and rescue our comrades!
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Noble Kasaro: If the remnants of an old fool's dream are
necessary for your future, feel free to use as much as you
need.

Noble Kasaro: Welcome! So, what kind of troublesome matter
do you have to discuss today?

Clea: It's about the series of murder cases happening in
Mucos.

Noble Kasaro: Some of us attended the funerals, of course,
but the cause of death was kept hidden.

Noble Kasaro: I don't mean to defile the deceased, but there
wasn't a single person with good behavior, to put it
politely.

Clea: What do you mean by 'not a single person with good
behavior'...?

Noble Kasaro: I have reservations about telling you this...
but it seems that those involved in the murders were all
individuals who enjoyed buying women.

Clea (That murder scene too... Could it be that the culprit
is disguising themselves as a prostitute?)

Noble Kasaro: I think it's pointless to say, but please
refrain from getting involved in anything too dangerous.
Clea: Yes, I will definitely come back alive.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Noble Kasaro: You always do reckless things, so if possible,
I want you to be considerate of the old folks' hearts.

Noble Kasaro: Welcome! I heard that the incident in Myukos
has been resolved.
Noble Kasaro: Who is the person behind you?

Thief Nora: They said they saw the place where the blue
overlaps together, fighting in the same location as your
son!

Cors the Wanderer: Allow me to explain first. I am a member
of the criminal organization in Myukos.

Cors the Wanderer: I am someone who is not in a position to
speak with noble Kasaro.

Noble Kasaro: I don't quite understand, but... does our
respective positions matter when it comes to talking with my
son's friend?

Noble Kasaro: Never mind that, do you like tea? I have a
brand that my son used to drink often, shall I prepare it
for you?
Cors the Wanderer: I have lost, I surrender.
Clea: I feel like I'm intruding.

Thief Nora: Shouldn't we report the whole incident to the
shrine maiden?
Clea: Yes, let's go and introduce ourselves.

Cors the Wanderer: You all will probably get involved in
troublesome matters anyway, right?

Cors the Wanderer: Please let me know when that time comes.
Well then, everyone, take care.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
実績 思い出が重なる場所

Noble Kasaro: You always do reckless things, so if possible,
I want you to be considerate of the old folks' hearts.

Noble Kasaro: It's ironic that the fact that I had dreamed
of the Senate and gathered forces from reliable sources is
now proving to be useful.
Clea: I came from the Adventurer's Guild.

Noble Kasaro: Oh my, a customer from Futeira. Agonia has
sent quite a young one.

Noble Kasaro: Straight to the point, but I want you all to
go negotiate.
Clea: Is this about negotiating to secure a route?

Noble Kasaro: The land called Valt is unique, with both
long-time residents and nobles who have arrived later living
together.

Noble Kasaro: Because of that, there are many private lands
and too many roads that cannot be used freely.

Clea: I understand the situation. Where should I go for the
negotiations?

Noble Kasaro: Yes, first, I want you to go to the leader of
the Bulk Corps, Goat. If that doesn't work... I want you to
go to the noble Luid.
Noble Kasaro: I am waiting for good news.

\CL Area Liberation\c[18]\CL Valt Region/Bulk Corps Hunting
Ground\c[0]

Noble Kasaro: Oh, you're back! So, did the negotiations go
well?
Clea: We can make use of Lord Luid's land, the noble's.

Noble Kasaro: Well done! As expected of the Adventurer's
Guild, we are one step closer to our dream!

Noble Kasaro: Ah, just in time! After the crystal transport,
I'll have you all help as well.

Noble Kasaro: An unseen miracle...! Hahaha, I can't help but
get excited despite my age.

Clea: Please make a request to the Adventurer's Guild. I
will definitely come to help at that time.

Noble Kasaro: First, let's start with the crystal transport.
Once we are prepared here, I will request assistance from
the Adventurer's Guild.

Noble Kasaro: Please wait for a moment, and let me express
my respect for your hard work!

Noble Kasaro: Oh, you all came too! The preparations are
progressing with Caros-kun at the center.
Clea: When will we be taking off?

Noble Kasaro: I have discussed it with them as well... We
are planning to take off from the dock before dawn.
Thief Nora: Hey, isn't it dangerous to fly at night...?

Noble Kasaro: To avoid being seen by the citizens... more
than anything, there is something we absolutely must see.

Noble Kasaro: Rest until night, everyone. Consider the
luxurious meal we had so far as a token of gratitude!
Thief Nora: Yay! Thank you very much!

Clea: It's been a while since we had a leisurely meal like
this.

Thief Nora: Wow, this is amazing! The bread is, um, really
impressive!

Mage Relm: Please calm down, Nora-san. Don't take mine,
okay!

Priestess Sophia: Hehe, delicious sake is wonderful. Well,
except for the fact that everything I usually drink now
tastes like dirty water.

Thief Nora: The ship I saw before can fly in the sky,
right?! I never imagined I could have such an experience!

Thief Nora: I'm glad I followed Clea-san! I never imagined I
could eat such fluffy bread, mmmph!
Clea: Was it a good decision to follow me...?

Clea: I never even thought about something like that... To
have someone appreciate my actions for the sake of my own
goals.

Mage Relm: I'm grateful for our connection with the
Adventurer's Guild! As a genius like me being part of the
team, I should be the one receiving thanks.

Priestess Sophia: I wonder if Eleo-chan would be surprised
if I told her that we flew in the sky. Maybe I should tell
her when we return... Oh, everyone...

Priestess Sophia: We're not parting ways just yet, you know?
Hehe, so please don't make that kind of face.

Mage Relm: I-I'm not making that kind of face! Once I defeat
the dragon, I'll return to the academy, so...

Thief Nora: U-Um, if I also obtain the dragon's eye, there's
a place I need to deliver it to... S-So... ugh...
Clea: If I... defeat the dragon...
Mansion Maid: Welcome to Lord Casaro's mansion.

Mansion Maid: Have you been to the Kasaro Bathhouse? It's a
wonderful place, so you should definitely go and check it
out.

Mansion Maid: Have you been to the Kasaro Bathhouse? It's a
wonderful place, so you should definitely go and check it
out.

Captain Clevo: Don't push yourself too hard. Let's keep
living, not just for ourselves, but for our fallen comrades.
Captain Clevo: If anything happens, be sure to let me know.
